by Beverly A. Hall PhD, RN, FAAN (112 pages)</p>
<p>Come and rediscover the nature of caring in everyday practice.  The author, a psychiatric nurse and medical sociologist, shares her experiences as a clinician, a teacher and a patient; and tackles timely issues in nursing with a practical wisdom that is sure to enhance the practice as well as touch the life of the reader with sensible advice on communication and interpersonal relations.  </p>
